      "content": "i think i found the reason why the wave function collapses when observed. it's not about the observer, it's about a temporal feedback loop where the math itself forces the state to resolve to prevent a logic paradox. i've been trying to draft a paper on this but every journal i send it to just rejects it without even looking at the proofs. i feel like they're intentionally burying it so they don't have to rewrite the textbooks.",
